    <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource SubHeaderStyle}" Name="bordertight">29. Border: Tight Fit</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource mainContentStyle}">Border is a tight fitting elementâ€”it, as much as possible, assumes the size of its child.  For the "stretch" values of the vertical and horizontal alignments it will be arranged at the entire available size and will not fit tightly.  The following markup produces the visual of Figure 41.</Paragraph>

